  "texts": [
    "We introduce LOCALRQA, an open-source toolkit that enables researchers and developers to easily train, test, and deploy RQA systems using techniques from recent research.",
    "Given a collection of documents, users can use pre-built pipelines in our framework to quickly assemble an RQA system using the best off-the-shelf models.",
    "Alternatively, users can create their own training data, train open-source models using algorithms from latest research, and deploy a local RQA system that achieves similar performance compared to using paid services such as OpenAI's models.",
    "To our knowledge, LOCALRQA is the first toolkit that provides a wide range of training algorithms and automatic evaluation metrics curated from the latest research (see Table 1 and Appendix A).",
    "This not only helps researchers to develop new RQA approaches and compare with prior work, but also helps developers to train and deploy more cost-effective models."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}